        <div id="cont_right">
		<p><a href="images/tut_img/worldgen3.jpg" rel="lightbox" title="World Generator"><img  width="50%" class="right" src="images/tut_img/worldgen3.jpg"/></a>Here we have my first 7 dwarves, all with no <a href="http://dwarffortresswiki.org/index.php/Skills">skills</a>.  Hitting TAB, we also have a default set of gear which we will adjust a bit, and lastly, no animals added on yet.  Keep in mind that any dwarf can technically do any job, as long as you designate it for them (through Dwarf Therapist, preferably).  These skill points simply boost a stat or two for certain dwarves.  A list of skills is also available on the wiki, as well as descriptions of each skill.  Note that some are, right now, USELESS… or very close to useless.</p>
		<p>Arrow left and right to switch between the dwarf and his skills, and + and – to distribute them.  There are two or three screens worth of skills, so scroll up and down.  If you want to go into great detail, you can also “v”iew each dwarf to see their personalities, appearance, and capabilities!  The only time this is of great importance is when choosing a leader / book keeper, and fighting dwarves.  Almost everyone else can suffice at most other jobs.  Dwarven attributes cannot be changed.</p>
